This paper deals with the problem of inferring an LTL specification from demonstrated behavior trajectories in MDPs, which is a problem in the field of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves optimization and genetic programming, which are topics in the fields of machine learning and robotics, respectively, making cs.LG and cs.RO likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with system design and control, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SY. Finally, the paper involves programming languages and formal methods, which are topics in the field of programming languages, making cs.PL a possible sub-category.
